{% block doc_content %}
    <h1>Installation & Setup</h1>
    <p>
        Getting started with Rhapsody is designed to be a quick and straightforward process.
        Follow these steps to get your local development environment up and running.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Server Requirements</h2>
    <p>Rhapsody is built with modern PHP. Please ensure your environment meets the following requirements:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>PHP 8.2 or higher</li>
        <li>Composer installed</li>
        <li>A local server environment like MAMP, WAMP, or Laravel Herd</li>
        <li>A MySQL-compatible database</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Installation</h2>
    <p>Clone the repository and install the Composer dependencies.</p>
    <pre><code># In your terminal
git clone https://github.com/arout77/Rhapsody-Framework your-site-name
cd your-site-name
composer install
cp .env.example .env
Set up your DB connection in the newly created .env file</code></pre>

    <h2>3. Environment Configuration</h2>
    <p>Rhapsody uses a <code>.env</code> file to manage environment-specific variables like database credentials. This keeps your secrets out of version control.</p>
    <p>First, copy the example file:</p>
    <pre><code>cp .env.example .env</code></pre>
    <p>Next, open the newly created <code>.env</code> file and configure it for your local machine. The most important variables are for the database connection:</p>
    <pre><code># .env
APP_BASE_URL="/your-site-name"

DB_HOST="127.0.0.1"
DB_PORT="3306"
DB_NAME="rhapsody_db"
DB_USER="root"
DB_PASS="root"</code></pre>

    <h2>4. Database Setup</h2>
    <p>You will need to create a database with the name you specified in your <code>.env</code> file (e.g., <code>rhapsody_db</code>).</p>
    <p>If you wish to receive email notifications regarding software updates and other relevant news, put your email address in the <code>MAIL_ADMIN_EMAIL</code> variable.</p>
